The candidate for the C&amp;S RE (Overall Co-ordinator) shall possess the following
minimum qualifications and practical experience stipulated below:
1. At least 12 years of relevant working experience in local building construction.
2. Accredited as C&amp;S Resident Engineer with the Joint Accreditation Committee of the Institution of Engineers Singapore (IES) and the Association of Consulting Engineers Singapore (ACES).
3. To possess and demonstrate track record(s) of being an Overall coordinator/ team leader for a team of Site Supervisors for projects with a value of building works &gt; $75 million.
4. Proficient in using Microsoft Word, Excel, and Powerpoint.
5. Demonstrate effective interpersonal skills, able to communicate effectively with various project stakeholders.
6. Familiarity with Building Control Regulations 2003, Part III on “Duties of Qualified Persons, Site Supervisors, and Builders During Construction”
7. Familiarity with the Public Service Sector Conditions of Contract (PSSCOC) for Construction Works

Note- you must submit the RE certificate.

Please include the following information in the resume
1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment
2) Last drawn and/or current salary in Singapore Dollar
3) Expected salary in Singapore Dollar
4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period
5) A current photograph
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and only short-listed candidates will be notified